mediaNotes: 2cy male singing from a box elder about 20 feet above me. It remained on a dead branch the entire time it was singing, except for the very last song which was given in the vegetation, before the bird flew off. Aged as a 2nd calendar-year by limited chestnut on sides and messy appearance. Had not yet started molting into basic.

This CSWA was singing the whole time we were n the picnic area.  Mainly from a yellow buckeye above the top of the parking lot, but in these recordings, he came down to forage in rhodo and mountain laurel.  For the second part odf the recording, he was right above my head.
